[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       1199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Error handling and retries.** Every external call (PubMed API, Comprehend Medical, SageMaker, Neptune) can fail. Production code wraps each in try/except with exponential backoff, dead-letter queues for persistent failures, and alerting when error rates spike. A single failed article shouldn't crash the batch. The architecture companion describes the DLQ pattern in detail: when a Step Functions execution fails after retries, the article ID and failure metadata land in an SQS dead letter queue with a CloudWatch alarm on queue depth and a reprocessor Lambda for replay.
